&lt;b&gt;The clergy of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church (UOC) do not want Russia to &quot;protect&quot; it&lt;/b&gt;

The clergy of the UOC &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/photo?fbid=688925040558437&amp;amp;set=a.131275086323438&quot;&gt;published&lt;/a&gt; an open letter on Facebook against Russia&#x27;s demand in its memorandum &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill/10252&quot;&gt;that Ukraine remove all restrictions on the UOC&lt;/a&gt;.

&lt;i&gt;&quot;The exploitation of this topic looks particularly treacherous, given the fact that it is our Church that has suffered the most among all religious organizations as a result of the military aggression of the Russian Federation,&quot;&lt;/i&gt; the statement says.

It emphasizes that the fruits of the self-proclaimed &quot;peacekeepers&quot; were thousands of killed and maimed UOC believers, hundreds of destroyed and damaged religious buildings, &lt;i&gt;&quot;the annexation of entire dioceses in the temporarily occupied territories in circumvention of the norms of canon law&quot;.&lt;/i&gt;

&lt;i&gt;&quot;We need to be protected primarily from Russia itself, which is what our believers and all concerned Ukrainians are doing as part of the Armed Forces of Ukraine, the State Emergency Service, volunteer communities, and at the level of all initiatives aimed at defending Ukraine,&quot;&lt;/i&gt; the statement says.

