In general, writes the UOC hierarch, with its shelling of Ukrainian cities, &lt;i&gt;&quot;Russia has once again shown its true face - the face of evil, ruthlessly bringing death and suffering to the civilian population&quot;.&lt;/i&gt;

&lt;i&gt;&quot;We will never agree with evil. But we will not break. For God is with us,&quot;&lt;/i&gt; Evlogiy said, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/Evlogiy/posts/pfbid0YHmk4N2sdTD1wNfy4nBYaU8BQiqsjLCD5V9CztD28h62ADFvGcMZnLBQuSHbCFu8l?__cft__[0]=AZXhwwDmc_IA5RBOcrFzN3AZm4_t9-9C-FkGlp8if6CMFWN6pKHQDiudUmKcTi2sIqlgjYFYJl4C85Ag9nnetOAGX1ouQYrSBHphcgNlZikoJH6gp8gP0sxGBB1sA0EH6ICQx4Qsmq4ASVMAuOroqe_5qOLcMipW6P0IsKV5JRSpEpAt1zpJVFDNuZikroY83iY&amp;amp;__tn__=%2CO%2CP-R&quot;&gt;commenting&lt;/a&gt; on the June 3 shelling of Sumy, which killed 4 people and injured 28.

