&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;A journalist from SOTAvision was detained today after filming Navalny&#x27;s grave - released on a pledge to appear.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A correspondent from the SOTAvision publication was detained in her own entrance today after she filmed the cemetery with Alexei Navalny&#x27;s grave. The security forces claimed that the reason for the detention was suspicion of cooperation with the Telegram channel &quot;Sirena&quot;, associated with the politician&#x27;s team.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The journalist was taken to the police station and interrogated. Her phone was confiscated and they searched for evidence of a connection with &quot;Sirena&quot;, but found nothing. Later, she was &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/sotavisionmedia/46913&quot;&gt;released&lt;/a&gt; on a pledge to appear - possibly to draw up a protocol on participation in the activities of an &quot;undesirable&quot; organization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason for the persecution was the photographs published in &quot;Sirena&quot;, which had previously appeared in the SOTAvision channel.&lt;/p&gt;

