&lt;b&gt;There is a heightened alert mode near the Radost-Skorbyashchenskiy parish in Minsk.&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The entire shoulder of the road from the turn from Pritytskogo Street to Yefrosinii Polotskoy Street and up to the Yestoday sports club is completely cleared of cars. Parking lots are blocked, &quot;No Stopping&quot; signs are installed. The parish gates are closed, a police car is on duty.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attempts by believers to enter the territory are accompanied by warnings: they cannot stay for long. All - parishioners, staff and clergy - are informed that in the near future they will have to leave the territory. A check of the premises of the temple complex by special services is expected in connection with the preparation for the visit of Patriarch Kirill, which is &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision/4475&quot;&gt;expected&lt;/a&gt; after 19:00.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tomorrow is the day of remembrance of St. Euphrosyne of Polotsk, and for the Radost-Skorbyashchenskiy parish this is a special day: one of the temples of the complex is consecrated in her honor, so the holiday is the patronal feast. A solemn all-night vigil was supposed to be served in the small church today. The parish schedule &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sobor.by/raspisanie.pdf&quot;&gt;indicates&lt;/a&gt; that the beginning of the service, which takes about two hours, is at 18:00. However, now the service is being hastily moved to an earlier time, since by 19:00 no one should remain on the territory of the temple complex.&lt;/p&gt;

